t62.text: Most herbivores make nearly all their own b12 via symbiotic gut bacteria. At times that doesn't work properly and farmers can use b12 supliments for a short time until the root cause is treated.

t63.text: It depends on how animals graze. Would the grassland of Africa be better off without the herbivores? No, they are part of a symbiotic relationship between grass and herbivore. Without the grazing, dung, trampling and urine grassland don't funtion properly.

t64.text: Even in the US where most of their beef is grain finished, most of what they eat is fodder/pasture during the cow calf phase. The rumen/gut of herbivores stays inoculated throughout their lives. Without gut flora they don't digest food and diepic.twitter.com/hVRWImUTEb
